( $w$) .

$$L(a(x), y) = \log(1 + \exp(-y\langle w, x\rangle)), \quad y \in \{-1, 1\}$$

.

$$df(w) = \frac{1}{1+exp(-y\langle 2,x\rangle )} d(exp(-y \langle w,x\rangle ))$$

$d(exp(-y \langle w,x\rangle)) = d(-y \langle w,x\rangle)exp(-y \langle w,x\rangle) = -yd(\langle w,x\rangle)exp(-y \langle w,x\rangle) = -y(\langle dw,x\rangle)exp(-y\langle w,x\rangle)$ , : $$\nabla f(w) =\frac{exp(-yw^Tx)}{1+exp(-yw^Tx)}(-yx)$$

In [397]:
class Preprocesser:
    def __init__(self):
        self.lemmatizer = nltk.stem.WordNetLemmatizer()
        
    def get_wordnet_pos(self, word):
        tag = nltk.pos_tag([word])[0][1][0].upper()
        tag_dict = {"J": wordnet.ADJ,
                "N": wordnet.NOUN,
                "V": wordnet.VERB,
                "R": wordnet.ADV}
        return tag_dict.get(tag, wordnet.NOUN)
        
    def __call__(self, text):


        lemmas = [
            self.lemmatizer.lemmatize(token, self.get_wordnet_pos(token))
            for token in text.split()
        ]

    
        return ' '.join(lemmas)
